00057 /*
00058  * Definition of Coordinate Systems. 
00059  * We follow the International Astronomical Union 1976/FK-5 conventions
00060  * (IAU-76/FK5). E.g. see Vallado, "Fundamentals of Astrodynamics and
00061  * Applications" Third Edition, 2007.  The newer IAU-2000 theory has similar
00062  * (but different in details) formulae from these -- be careful not to mix
00063  * them.
00064  */

00133 #define WGS84_COORDS    6   // World Geodetic System 1984 (WGS84)
00134 #define IRTF_COORDS     6   // ( aka International Terrestrial Reference Frame)
00135 #define GEO_COORDS      6   // ( aka "GEO" coords -- my term )
00136                             // (WGS84 and ITRF are not *exactly* the same, but
00137                             // supposedly agree at the cm level and within
00138                             // uncertainties of WGS84 are often considered to
00139                             // be equivelant)
00140                             //
00141                             // This is a truely Earth-fixed system. It's Z-axis
00142                             // is the true International Reference Pole and
00143                             // Meridian. And these are fixed in the crust of
00144                             // the Earth.  To go from PEF to WGS84, you need to
00145                             // know the angular offsets of the true pole from
00146                             // the PEF pole. These angle,  (xp and yp) are part
00147                             // of the so-called Earth-Observing-Parameters
00148                             // (EOP). They cant be predicted ahead of time, so
00149                             // we often just assume they are zero.  Ignoring
00150                             // them can introduce offsets on the ground of
00151                             // about 10m or so. The WGS84 system is the sytem
00152                             // that most GPS equipment uses(check?). Note also
00153                             // that geodetic latitude is defined differently
00154                             // from geocenteric latitude due to the flattening
00155                             // of the Earth in the z-direction. If the EOP values
00156                             // are not applied then WGS84 is same as PEF.
00157                             // Transformation:
00158                             //      Uwgs84 = Ry(-xp)Rz(-yp) Upef
00159 
00160 
00161 #define GSE_COORDS      7   // Geocentric Solar Ecliptic (mean of date quantities?)
00162 
00163 #define GSM_COORDS      8   // Geocentric Solar Magnetospheric (X to sun, mag dipole in X-Z plane)
00164 
00165 #define SM_COORDS       9   // Solar Magnetic (Mag dipole in Z, sun in X-Z plane)
00166 
00167 #define EDMAG_COORDS   10   // Eccentric Dipole Coords (true dipole is offset from center)
00168 
00169 #define CDMAG_COORDS   11   // Centered Dipole Coords
